Package: autoconf2.13
Version: 2.13
Revision: 1
Depends: m4
Conflicts: autoconf (<< 2.13-4), autoconf2.54 (<< 2.54-2), autoconf2.5 (<< 2.57-2)
Replaces: autoconf (<< 2.13-4), autoconf2.54 (<< 2.54-2), autoconf2.5 (<< 2.57-2)
Source: mirror:gnu:autoconf/autoconf-%v.tar.gz
Patch: %n.patch
Source-MD5: 9de56d4a161a723228220b0f425dc711
ConfigureParams: --infodir=%p/share/info --program-suffix="-%v"
InstallScript: <<
 make install prefix=%i infodir=%i/share/info
 mkdir -p %i/share/doc/%n
 install -m 644 README COPYING AUTHORS NEWS %i/share/doc/%n/
 mv %i/share/info/autoconf.info %i/share/info/autoconf-%v.info
 mv %i/share/info/standards.info %i/share/info/standards-%v.info
<<
PostInstScript: <<
 update-alternatives --install %p/bin/autoconf autoconf %p/bin/autoconf-%v 213
 update-alternatives --install %p/bin/autoheader autoheader %p/bin/autoheader-%v 213
 update-alternatives --install %p/bin/autoreconf autoreconf %p/bin/autoreconf-%v 213
 update-alternatives --install %p/bin/autoscan autoscan %p/bin/autoscan-%v 213
 update-alternatives --install %p/bin/autoupdate autoupdate %p/bin/autoupdate-%v 213
 update-alternatives --install %p/bin/ifnames ifnames %p/bin/ifnames-%v 213
 update-alternatives --install %p/share/autoconf autoconf-dir %p/share/autoconf-%v 213
 update-alternatives --install %p/share/info/autoconf.info autoconf.info %p/share/info/autoconf-%v.info 213
 update-alternatives --install %p/share/info/standards.info standards.info %p/share/info/autoconf-%v.info 213
<<
PostRmScript: <<
 if [ "$1" != "upgrade" ]; then
  update-alternatives --remove autoconf %p/bin/autoconf-%v
  update-alternatives --remove autoheader %p/bin/autoheader-%v
  update-alternatives --remove autoreconf %p/bin/autoreconf-%v
  update-alternatives --remove autoscan %p/bin/autoscan-%v
  update-alternatives --remove autoupdate %p/bin/autoupdate-%v
  update-alternatives --remove ifnames %p/bin/ifnames-%v
  update-alternatives --remove autoconf-dir %p/share/autoconf-%v
  update-alternatives --remove autoconf.info %p/share/info/autoconf-%v.info
  update-alternatives --remove standards.info %p/share/info/standards-%v.info
 fi
<<
InfoDocs: autoconf-%v.info standards-%v.info
#
Description: System for generating configure scripts, v2.13
DescDetail: <<
GNU Autoconf is a package for generating configure scripts.
These scripts are present in a large number of free software packages
and are used to detect system features at compilation time.

This package installs Autoconf 2.13. There are newer versions
available, but there are some compatibility problems and some packages
require version 2.13. To get one of the new versions, install the
autoconf25 package instead.
<<
